Following sustained bargain hunting in most blue-chip stocks, trading on the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE), reopened upbeat, yesterday, causing the All-Share Index (ASI), to rise by 0.05 per cent. At the close of transactions Monday, the ASI increased by 13.64 absolute points or 0.05 per cent growth to close at 25,605.59 points. Similarly, the overall market capitalisation gained N7 billion to close at N13.358 trillion.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .